rComments: He's a funny guy and goes into great detail during his lectures. He writes a bit too much on each slide but it's easy to filter out the important info from the unnecessary stuff. I've only gotten one assignment back so far but I got a good grade on it, though I suppose I should thank my TA for that. Overall he's a good prof.

My favourite teacher in this university. The only thing that one can possibly complain about him is his dense lecture slides that seem to contain almost too much historical details for a undergrad course, which can appear scary at first sight. However you do NOT have to remember everything unless you want to. And he is a very lenient marker.
